- And, uh...

267
00:15:27,143 --> 00:15:30,537
And these are drawings
by my daughter, Jia.

268
00:15:30,711 --> 00:15:34,411
And you're gonna think
that I'm completely insane.

269
00:15:34,585 --> 00:15:37,109
No, the patterns are the same
in the middle section.

270
00:15:37,283 --> 00:15:39,937
Yes. Exactly.

271
00:15:40,111 --> 00:15:41,852
[sighs] Thank you.

272
00:15:42,027 --> 00:15:43,375
Look, our analysts,

273
00:15:43,549 --> 00:15:44,990
they don't know
what to make of this.

274
00:15:45,029 --> 00:15:46,205
They're talking in circles,

275
00:15:46,379 --> 00:15:47,778
they're saying
"radio interference,"

276
00:15:47,815 --> 00:15:49,294
"coincidence," but I...

277
00:15:49,469 --> 00:15:51,384
I know that you think
outside of the box.

278
00:15:51,557 --> 00:15:53,559
[chuckles] I didn't know
who else to turn to.

279
00:15:53,734 --> 00:15:55,171
And they sent you
here because...?

280
00:15:55,345 --> 00:15:56,625
No, no one sent me.
I came here on my...

281
00:15:56,649 --> 00:15:57,889
You know, that's what's ironic.

282
00:15:57,956 --> 00:15:59,349
You know,
Monarch wouldn't confirm

283
00:15:59,523 --> 00:16:01,240
my crucial part
in taking down Mechagodzilla,

284
00:16:01,264 --> 00:16:03,134
which cost me thousands of...

285
00:16:03,308 --> 00:16:05,311
hundreds of subscribers
on my blog.

286
00:16:05,485 --> 00:16:07,312
Oh, and the trolls...
[chuckles]

287
00:16:07,486 --> 00:16:08,767
the trolls online, they question

288
00:16:08,836 --> 00:16:10,115
every single thing
that I put up.

289
00:16:10,273 --> 00:16:12,404
Especially this one troll.

290
00:16:12,578 --> 00:16:13,938
This one troll named
ghidorastan64.

291
00:16:14,058 --> 00:16:15,321
You ever heard of him?

292
00:16:15,495 --> 00:16:16,820
- No, I don't think I have.
- Great,

293
00:16:16,844 --> 00:16:18,280
because he's a trash bag, okay?

294
00:16:18,455 --> 00:16:19,779
I'm more qualified
than half of those people

295
00:16:19,803 --> 00:16:21,083
that you have working
over there.

296
00:16:21,197 --> 00:16:22,596
I knew what Godzilla
was going to do

297
00:16:22,763 --> 00:16:24,200
before anybody
at Monarch said...

298
00:16:24,374 --> 00:16:26,549
Which is why I am here,
Bernie. [chuckles]

299
00:16:26,724 --> 00:16:28,552
I am here. Okay?

300
00:16:31,510 --> 00:16:32,990
Can you help me or not?

301
00:16:33,904 --> 00:16:35,298
That depends.

302
00:16:35,471 --> 00:16:36,995
Are you the new boss
down at the Mess?

303
00:16:37,168 --> 00:16:38,431
The what?

304
00:16:38,605 --> 00:16:39,911
The Monarch
Hollow Earth Station.

305
00:16:40,085 --> 00:16:41,782
The MHES, the Mess.

306
00:16:41,956 --> 00:16:43,174
Yeah, nobody calls it that.

307
00:16:43,349 --> 00:16:45,221
I run the Kong research division

308
00:16:45,394 --> 00:16:47,831
but technically
Director Hampton is in charge

309
00:16:48,005 --> 00:16:49,834
- of general operations.
- Hmm.

310
00:16:50,008 --> 00:16:51,506
Well, Director Hampton
doesn't have a kid

311
00:16:51,530 --> 00:16:52,750
who can talk to Kong.

312
00:16:57,188 --> 00:16:58,842
You want to go to Hollow Earth.

313
00:16:59,017 --> 00:17:00,472
[gasps excitedly] I'm so glad
I didn't have to say it.

314
00:17:00,496 --> 00:17:02,019
I thought you were never
gonna ask

315
00:17:02,193 --> 00:17:03,779
- but I really do need proof.
- No, I'm not asking.

316
00:17:03,803 --> 00:17:05,478
I mean, that would help me
with my bona fides

317
00:17:05,501 --> 00:17:07,000
for my blog. And I knew
that you would be the person

318
00:17:07,025 --> 00:17:08,741
- to help me do that.
- [cell phone buzzing]

319
00:17:08,766 --> 00:17:10,003
Okay. Well, if this happens,
and that is a big if,

320
00:17:10,028 --> 00:17:11,682
then Monarch would need,
you know,

321
00:17:11,855 --> 00:17:13,398
whatever you guys call it.
Final cut on anything in...

322
00:17:13,423 --> 00:17:15,182
[Bernie] Whoa. I'm sorry,
final cut? No, no, no.

323
00:17:15,207 --> 00:17:16,792
You know, that will destroy
my journalistic integrity.

324
00:17:16,817 --> 00:17:18,818
Shit.

325
00:17:18,992 --> 00:17:20,188
No really true, good
documentarian gives final cut.

326
00:17:20,211 --> 00:17:21,560
I could make you a producer.

327
00:17:21,734 --> 00:17:23,234
Okay, okay! Fine! Final cut!
Final cut! Fine!

328
00:17:23,259 --> 00:17:24,539
Look, something is happening
to my daughter,

329
00:17:24,564 --> 00:17:27,306
and I have no idea
how to fix it.

330
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:29,090
You work out what's going on,

331
00:17:29,265 --> 00:17:30,048
and I will get you anything
that you want, okay?

332
00:17:30,221 --> 00:17:31,483
That is a promise.

333
00:17:31,657 --> 00:17:32,876
Well, anything is a lot,

334
00:17:33,050 --> 00:17:34,487
but that's very generous,
but I...

335
00:17:34,661 --> 00:17:37,010
- And we have to go. Right now.
- What?

336
00:17:37,185 --> 00:17:38,796
Godzilla is on the move again.

337
00:17:38,970 --> 00:17:40,798
[ominous music playing]

338
00:17:46,673 --> 00:17:48,066
[dramatic music playing]

339
00:17:52,809 --> 00:17:54,463
[roaring]

340
00:18:09,260 --> 00:18:11,001
[roaring]

341
00:18:24,537 --> 00:18:26,712
[distant rumbling]

342
00:18:26,886 --> 00:18:28,498
[suspenseful music playing]

343
00:18:35,287 --> 00:18:37,070
[Ilene] Okay, listen to me.

344
00:18:37,246 --> 00:18:38,701
If Godzilla's on the move,
he senses a threat coming.

345
00:18:38,724 --> 00:18:40,249
We don't know what it is.

346
00:18:40,423 --> 00:18:41,661
[man on phone]
And you're not concerned?

347
00:18:41,684 --> 00:18:43,045
Of course we're concerned,
Senator.

348
00:18:43,164 --> 00:18:44,991
That's why we're monitoring
the situation.

349
00:18:45,166 --> 00:18:45,863
[Senator] Monitor the fact
that if Godzilla heads...

350
00:18:46,037 --> 00:18:47,472
What is it? You just...

351
00:18:47,646 --> 00:18:48,125
-And I am telling you,
-We have a problem!

352
00:18:48,299 --> 00:18:49,605
Senator...

353
00:18:49,779 --> 00:18:51,259
that Kong doesn't
leave Hollow Earth.

354
00:18:51,433 --> 00:18:54,872
Which is why Godzilla has
no reason to retaliate.

355
00:18:55,046 --> 00:18:56,177
[alarm blaring]

356
00:18:58,048 --> 00:19:00,050
[dramatic music playing]

357
00:19:01,878 --> 00:19:03,096
[grunts]

358
00:19:03,271 --> 00:19:05,186
[indistinct chatter]

359
00:19:06,578 --> 00:19:08,451
- What's he doing up here?
- No idea.

360
00:19:08,625 --> 00:19:10,625
- Well, does Godzilla know?
- Not that we can tell.

361
00:19:10,757 --> 00:19:12,454
Yeah, well, it's only
a matter of time.

362
00:19:12,628 --> 00:19:15,153
And what happens if Godzilla
starts heading this way?

363
00:19:15,326 --> 00:19:17,023
Then we all run like hell.

364
00:19:17,199 --> 00:19:18,262
[Monarch agent]
Get up, let's go!

365
00:19:18,287 --> 00:19:19,487
Keep it up. Come on. Let's go.

366
00:19:27,512 --> 00:19:29,211
[groaning weakly]

367
00:19:34,085 --> 00:19:35,565
[in sign language]

368
00:19:37,697 --> 00:19:38,697
[Ilene sighs]

369
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:41,396
[groaning softly]

370
00:19:43,702 --> 00:19:45,965
[Ilene sighs]

371
00:19:46,140 --> 00:19:47,579
[Monarch agent 2]
Sedatives in place.

372
00:19:55,801 --> 00:19:57,126
[man over radio]
All right, the good news is

373
00:19:57,151 --> 00:19:58,761
it's just an infected tooth.

374
00:19:58,935 --> 00:20:02,461
But luckily, you've come
to the best doctor in town.

375
00:20:02,634 --> 00:20:04,420
["I Got'cha" playing
over stereo]

376
00:20:07,074 --> 00:20:08,162
[mouthing] ♪ I gotcha ♪

377
00:20:13,298 --> 00:20:16,519
♪ I gotcha ♪

378
00:20:16,692 --> 00:20:18,452
[Monarch agent] All right,
Kong sedation at a 100%.

379
00:20:18,477 --> 00:20:19,652
Vitals stable.

380
00:20:19,826 --> 00:20:21,349
Trapper, you are clear to swap

381
00:20:21,523 --> 00:20:22,848
the damaged tooth
with replacement.

382
00:20:22,873 --> 00:20:24,961
[buzzer sounds]

383
00:20:25,135 --> 00:20:27,529
Way-hey! [laughing]

384
00:20:30,054 --> 00:20:31,272
Touchdown, Trapper.

385
00:20:33,012 --> 00:20:34,798
[Kong snoring]

386
00:20:39,019 --> 00:20:40,019
[grunts]

387
00:20:41,892 --> 00:20:43,720
[Kong exhales]

388
00:20:43,894 --> 00:20:45,503
Whoa. Fella.

389
00:20:45,677 --> 00:20:46,877
What'd you have for breakfast?

390
00:20:48,507 --> 00:20:50,029
["I Got'cha" continues playing]

391
00:20:50,203 --> 00:20:51,204
[loudly] All right?

392
00:20:53,859 --> 00:20:55,688
Yeah, this sucker's ready
to come out.

393
00:20:56,602 --> 00:20:58,082
[whirring]

394
00:20:58,256 --> 00:20:59,387
Whoa.

395
00:21:00,605 --> 00:21:01,605
All right, let's roll!

396
00:21:01,693 --> 00:21:03,086
[engine accelerating]

397
00:21:03,260 --> 00:21:04,087
[tooth squelches]

398
00:21:04,261 --> 00:21:05,307
[Kong groans]

399
00:21:06,394 --> 00:21:07,874
[laughs]

400
00:21:08,048 --> 00:21:09,701
[door hissing]

401
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:11,400
[intriguing music playing]

402
00:21:23,890 --> 00:21:24,890
There she is.

403
00:21:25,718 --> 00:21:27,415
Trapper.

404
00:21:27,589 --> 00:21:29,219
Thanks for getting down here
so fast. Nice work.

405
00:21:29,242 --> 00:21:31,462
You are most welcome.

406
00:21:31,636 --> 00:21:32,997
It's not every day
you get to climb

407
00:21:33,073 --> 00:21:34,770
inside a 300-foot ape's mouth,
is it?

408
00:21:34,944 --> 00:21:36,791
Yeah. And you're sure it's
gonna be strong enough?

409
00:21:36,816 --> 00:21:37,948
The tooth? Yeah.

410
00:21:38,122 --> 00:21:39,515
That's the same
polymer composite

411
00:21:39,689 --> 00:21:41,101
they use on the vehicle
heat shields.

412
00:21:41,125 --> 00:21:42,473
[groans sadly]

413
00:21:42,647 --> 00:21:43,756
[Trapper]
He could chomp through

414
00:21:43,779 --> 00:21:45,172
the Eiffel Tower
with that thing.

415
00:21:45,346 --> 00:21:46,888
[chuckles] Well,
good teeth aren't gonna help

416
00:21:46,913 --> 00:21:48,611
if Godzilla senses
that he's up here.

417
00:21:48,785 --> 00:21:52,005
Well. You can't have a Titan
with a toothache,

418
00:21:52,179 --> 00:21:53,223
can you? [chuckles]

419
00:21:53,397 --> 00:21:54,703
- No.
- Don't worry.

420
00:21:54,877 --> 00:21:56,246
Couple of hours
he might be a bit groggy,

421
00:21:56,269 --> 00:21:58,097
but he'll be good to go
back down.

422
00:21:58,271 --> 00:21:59,597
You know, when I first heard
that you were gonna be a vet

423
00:21:59,622 --> 00:22:00,926
I thought no.

424
00:22:01,101 --> 00:22:02,493
That is way too boring

425
00:22:02,667 --> 00:22:04,278
- for Trapper.
- [chuckles]

426
00:22:04,452 --> 00:22:05,994
Then you go and become the
weirdest vet in the world.

427
00:22:06,019 --> 00:22:07,759
Yeah, it's basically
me and Doctor Dolittle.

428
00:22:07,933 --> 00:22:10,807
Except my animals are bigger.

429
00:22:10,980 --> 00:22:13,592
I thought finally, someone has
made him grow up.

430
00:22:13,766 --> 00:22:15,681
Nope. Someone tried that
back in college,

431
00:22:15,855 --> 00:22:18,380
- but... didn't really work.
- Oh, yeah?

432
00:22:18,554 --> 00:22:19,858
Yeah,
what was it she said to me?

433
00:22:20,032 --> 00:22:22,209
"Trapper,
you are not a serious person."

434
00:22:22,384 --> 00:22:23,423
Oh, she sounds very smart.

435
00:22:23,471 --> 00:22:26,474
Yeah, ish. She got a PhD.

436
00:22:26,648 --> 00:22:28,477
- Two, actually.
- [chuckles]

437
00:22:30,260 --> 00:22:32,132
How's the kid doing?

438
00:22:32,306 --> 00:22:35,134
[Ilene] You know. Struggling.

439
00:22:35,308 --> 00:22:37,310
Trying to find her place
in the world.

440
00:22:37,486 --> 00:22:40,140
Yeah, I know how that goes.

441
00:22:40,314 --> 00:22:42,272
Don't worry,
she'll be all right.

442
00:22:42,447 --> 00:22:43,448
She got a good mum.

443
00:22:46,277 --> 00:22:47,277
[in sign language]

444
00:22:49,976 --> 00:22:51,455
[groans softly]

445
00:22:56,374 --> 00:22:57,767
[grunts softly]

446
00:23:00,029 --> 00:23:04,425
Doctor Andrews. Your guest
has been asking for you.

447
00:23:06,863 --> 00:23:07,645
[Bernie] Please don't take this
the wrong way,

448
00:23:07,819 --> 00:23:09,605
but can I just say,

449
00:23:09,778 --> 00:23:11,538
that your research library
has many glaring omissions.

450
00:23:11,563 --> 00:23:12,962
I had to call in
some serious favors

451
00:23:12,999 --> 00:23:14,479
from my Discord chat.
They were not...

452
00:23:14,522 --> 00:23:15,872
Bernie, do you have something?

453
00:23:16,046 --> 00:23:17,371
Yes, I've got something.
I do have something.

454
00:23:17,394 --> 00:23:19,092
Whatever signal
you guys are picking up,

455
00:23:19,266 --> 00:23:21,419
okay, we have seen similar
patterns repeating over time.

456
00:23:21,442 --> 00:23:23,923
And each spike corresponds
with a specific Titan event.

457
00:23:24,096 --> 00:23:25,465
Can you hold this, please?
Thank you so much.

458
00:23:25,490 --> 00:23:27,449
Okay, check this out.

459
00:23:27,623 --> 00:23:30,364
See this? King Ghidorah, huh?
First encounter with Godzilla.

460
00:23:30,538 --> 00:23:31,538
- Mm-hmm.
- Here, uh,

461
00:23:31,670 --> 00:23:33,366
discovery of Skull Island.

462
00:23:33,541 --> 00:23:35,432
All right. So what you're
saying is that these signals

463
00:23:35,457 --> 00:23:37,173
- aren't just random patterns.
- Yeah, it seems that way, yes.

464
00:23:37,197 --> 00:23:38,547
And Godzilla's picking up on it?

465
00:23:38,721 --> 00:23:40,287
Oh, I can do you one better.
Now, look,

466
00:23:40,461 --> 00:23:41,902
I've looked
at points of similarities

467
00:23:42,028 --> 00:23:43,682
in each wave form
and I compared them

468
00:23:43,855 --> 00:23:44,596
- to that pattern, and...
- Bernie, what are you saying?

469
00:23:44,769 --> 00:23:46,205
It's a distress call!

470
00:23:46,380 --> 00:23:48,773
It's a distress call.
A psychic energy SOS.

471
00:23:48,948 --> 00:23:51,080
Now, if your daughter is
seeing these symbols,

472
00:23:51,255 --> 00:23:53,865
then something down
there is calling for help.

473
00:23:54,039 --> 00:23:55,119
[suspenseful music playing]

474
00:23:56,868 --> 00:23:58,567
[Ilene] Regular soundwaves,

475
00:23:58,740 --> 00:24:00,916
they can't propagate this far
without decay. This?

476
00:24:01,090 --> 00:24:03,010
This is something that
we have never encountered.

477
00:24:03,093 --> 00:24:05,292
- And it's getting stronger.
- You got a working theory?

478
00:24:05,442 --> 00:24:06,749
Yeah, telepathic alien language.

479
00:24:06,923 --> 00:24:08,576
It's some sort of
distress signal.

480
00:24:09,969 --> 00:24:11,362
Signal? From what?

481
00:24:11,536 --> 00:24:12,536
Or from who.

482
00:24:12,624 --> 00:24:13,885
Well, whatever it is,

483
00:24:14,059 --> 00:24:15,584
this is why Godzilla's
on the move?

484
00:24:15,758 --> 00:24:17,518
We can't say for sure.
But it seems that way.

485
00:24:17,673 --> 00:24:19,892
[Hampton] Well, we have
to figure this out fast.

486
00:24:20,066 --> 00:24:23,505
The wolves are already
at our door.

487
00:24:23,679 --> 00:24:25,047
The government has been
looking for an excuse

488
00:24:25,070 --> 00:24:26,898
to take over
Hollow Earth operations.

489
00:24:27,073 --> 00:24:28,901
And the corporations
are licking their chops.

490
00:24:29,075 --> 00:24:30,729
Yeah,
because who wants to be rich

491
00:24:30,903 --> 00:24:32,425
and get rid of all the monsters?

492
00:24:32,601 --> 00:24:34,298
I mean, that'd be terrible,
right?

493
00:24:34,471 --> 00:24:36,752
We'd better find the source
before D.C. gets wind of this.

494
00:24:37,387 --> 00:24:40,521
[sighs] Okay.

495
00:24:40,695 --> 00:24:42,914
I'm giving you
full operational oversight.

496
00:24:43,088 --> 00:24:45,134
Take a small team.
Mikael, make it fast

497
00:24:45,308 --> 00:24:46,788
and don't let anyone die.

498
00:24:46,962 --> 00:24:48,964
We'll be in and out of there
before nightfall.

499
00:24:49,138 --> 00:24:50,880
You, uh, you feel like
going for a ride?

500
00:24:52,445 --> 00:24:53,445
Thought you'd never ask.

501
00:24:54,623 --> 00:24:55,623
[dramatic music playing]

502
00:24:57,016 --> 00:24:58,626
[alarm blaring]

503
00:24:58,800 --> 00:25:00,386
[announcer over PA]
Attention, all hands.

504
00:25:00,411 --> 00:25:01,910
Prepare HEAV three
for Hollow Earth launch

505
00:25:01,933 --> 00:25:04,807
in T minus five minutes.

506
00:25:04,980 --> 00:25:07,001
[Mikael] There's no response
from the Hollow Earth outpost.

507
00:25:07,026 --> 00:25:08,201
Their radios must be down.

508
00:25:08,375 --> 00:25:09,654
Well, then
that's our first stop.

509
00:25:09,811 --> 00:25:10,811
[Mikael] Copy that.

510
00:25:12,117 --> 00:25:13,729
[in sign language]

511
00:25:19,778 --> 00:25:20,778
[sighs]

512
00:25:32,529 --> 00:25:34,663
- [alarm blaring]
- [sighs]

513
00:25:34,836 --> 00:25:36,795
All right, wakey wakey,
everyone. Kong's up.

514
00:25:38,623 --> 00:25:39,624
[grunting softly]

515
00:25:47,806 --> 00:25:49,634
[dramatic synth music playing]

516
00:25:57,336 --> 00:26:01,253
Hey. Hey! Doctor Andrews. Hey.
Come on, we had a deal!

517
00:26:01,428 --> 00:26:02,667
Bernie, this isn't sightseeing.

518
00:26:02,820 --> 00:26:03,971
It's a reconnaissance mission.

519
00:26:03,996 --> 00:26:06,390
[scoffs] So, I see how it is.

520
00:26:06,564 --> 00:26:08,173
When you need something,
it's all

521
00:26:08,347 --> 00:26:10,021
"you're so smart, Bernie,
you're so capable, Bernie,

522
00:26:10,046 --> 00:26:11,874
"I'll subscribe
to your Titan blog, Bernie,"

523
00:26:12,048 --> 00:26:14,833
and when I deliver it,
you toss me aside.

524
00:26:15,007 --> 00:26:17,053
Okay, look.
This could be dangerous.

525
00:26:17,227 --> 00:26:18,707
[scoffs] Come on.

526
00:26:18,881 --> 00:26:20,577
[chuckles]
I'm no stranger to danger.

527
00:26:22,449 --> 00:26:25,104
I didn't mean to rhyme
that time.

528
00:26:25,278 --> 00:26:28,280
Look, you owe me. Okay?
I helped crack this thing.

529
00:26:28,454 --> 00:26:30,477
This could be like last time,
when we saved the world.

530
00:26:30,500 --> 00:26:31,545
Remember? Hmm?

531
00:26:34,243 --> 00:26:35,593
- Mikael?
- Yeah.

532
00:26:36,724 --> 00:26:38,203
Prep a seat for one more.

533
00:26:38,377 --> 00:26:40,182
Thank you, Doctor Andrews!
You will not regret it.

534
00:26:40,205 --> 00:26:41,205
You're kidding, right?

535
00:26:42,948 --> 00:26:43,992
I'm the plus one. Hello.

536
00:26:45,167 --> 00:26:46,169
[sighs]

537
00:26:46,343 --> 00:26:47,736
[grunts]

538
00:26:47,910 --> 00:26:49,190
[automated voice]
Systems online.

539
00:26:49,346 --> 00:26:50,671
- Whoa. Oh. Whoa.
- [system powering up]

540
00:26:50,694 --> 00:26:52,479
We're online. [chuckles]

541
00:26:52,653 --> 00:26:54,307
We are going to Hollow Earth.

542
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:58,268
I am going to Hollow Earth.

543
00:26:58,442 --> 00:27:00,923
Oh, my God. What am I doing?

544
00:27:01,096 --> 00:27:02,551
So, is there, like,
a in-flight briefing

545
00:27:02,576 --> 00:27:03,857
that I should know about?
You know...

546
00:27:03,882 --> 00:27:05,317
- Yeah, there is.
- He's very...

547
00:27:05,491 --> 00:27:07,625
There's no parachutes,
no flotation devices,

548
00:27:07,798 --> 00:27:09,278
you touch any of this stuff,

549
00:27:09,452 --> 00:27:11,063
you lose your hand,
and if you die,

550
00:27:11,237 --> 00:27:12,717
make sure
it's outside my vehicle.

551
00:27:15,067 --> 00:27:18,330
Good briefing. Great briefing.

552
00:27:18,505 --> 00:27:20,246
Don't take Mikael
too personally.

553
00:27:20,420 --> 00:27:21,700
Aggression is his love language.

554
00:27:22,727 --> 00:27:23,728
[button clicks]

555
00:27:23,902 --> 00:27:25,208
["Twilight Zone" playing]

556
00:27:28,428 --> 00:27:30,778
All right, Mikael.
Let's punch it.

557
00:27:32,432 --> 00:27:34,130
[electricity buzzing]

558
00:27:35,566 --> 00:27:37,394
[yawning]

559
00:27:40,266 --> 00:27:41,416
[announcer over radio]
HEAV one,

560
00:27:41,441 --> 00:27:42,268
you are clear for launch.

561
00:27:42,442 --> 00:27:43,574
Let's do this.

562
00:27:44,662 --> 00:27:45,794
[engine thruster pulses]

563
00:27:45,968 --> 00:27:46,795
[Bernie grunts]

564
00:27:46,969 --> 00:27:47,970
[chuckles nervously]

565
00:27:50,102 --> 00:27:51,930
[Bernie screaming]

566
00:27:52,104 --> 00:27:53,758
[Bernie continues screaming]

567
00:27:53,932 --> 00:27:55,804
[panting]

568
00:27:55,978 --> 00:27:57,806
Just try not
to swallow your tongue.

569
00:27:57,980 --> 00:27:59,807
What?
Try not to swallow my tongue?

570
00:27:59,981 --> 00:28:01,175
I don't exactly know
what that means.

571
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:04,334
[Bernie panting]

572
00:28:04,508 --> 00:28:05,789
[announcer over radio]
Base to HEAV,

573
00:28:05,814 --> 00:28:07,336
you're clear for entry.

574
00:28:07,510 --> 00:28:08,685
On your count,

575
00:28:08,859 --> 00:28:10,122
- Doctor Andrews.
- Three.

576
00:28:10,296 --> 00:28:11,036
- All right, let's go.
- [Ilene] Two.

577
00:28:11,210 --> 00:28:12,558
[Bernie] I'm not ready.

578
00:28:12,733 --> 00:28:14,344
- [Ilene] And one.
- [Bernie] Oh, my God!

579
00:28:15,345 --> 00:28:16,999
[glitching]

580
00:28:18,521 --> 00:28:20,175
[vortex pulsing]

581
00:28:23,440 --> 00:28:24,441
[screaming]

582
00:28:27,791 --> 00:28:29,141
[breathing heavily]

583
00:28:29,315 --> 00:28:30,621
[Mikael screaming]

584
00:28:35,886 --> 00:28:38,411
[shrieking]

585
00:28:38,585 --> 00:28:44,374
[whimpering]
I'm turning into water.

586
00:28:44,548 --> 00:28:45,548
[distorted screaming]

587
00:28:47,550 --> 00:28:49,465
[distorted laughing]

588
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:50,640
[whoops]

589
00:28:50,771 --> 00:28:52,469
["Twilight Zone" resumes]

590
00:29:04,567 --> 00:29:05,916
[system powering up]

591
00:29:06,090 --> 00:29:07,744
[automated voice]
Flight systems active.

592
00:29:07,919 --> 00:29:09,528
- [panting]
- Systems stabilized.

593
00:29:09,702 --> 00:29:10,942
- [laughing]
- [Mikael] All systems good,

594
00:29:10,965 --> 00:29:12,125
- Doc.
- How's everyone doing?

595
00:29:12,183 --> 00:29:13,183
You all right?

596
00:29:13,271 --> 00:29:14,490
- Never better.
- Yeah?

597
00:29:14,664 --> 00:29:16,013
Bernie, you good?

598
00:29:18,538 --> 00:29:20,236
[grunts softly]

599
00:29:20,410 --> 00:29:23,194
- Nice one. [panting] Oh, wow.
- [Ilene] Whew.

600
00:29:23,368 --> 00:29:25,153
[dramatic synth music playing]

601
00:29:26,851 --> 00:29:28,983
[panting]

602
00:29:32,203 --> 00:29:33,770
[chuckles in disbelief]

603
00:29:44,955 --> 00:29:46,740
[Ilene] Looks like
Kong is headed home.

604
00:29:46,914 --> 00:29:48,761
- How far to the outpost?
- [Mikael] Hundred klicks.

605
00:29:48,786 --> 00:29:50,105
They're still
not answering comms.

606
00:29:52,397 --> 00:29:53,224
[automated voice]
Proximity alert.

607
00:29:53,398 --> 00:29:54,923
[creatures screeching]

608
00:29:55,096 --> 00:29:56,376
[Mikael] Predators,
nine o'clock.

609
00:29:56,532 --> 00:29:58,099
Where? What?

610
00:29:58,273 --> 00:29:59,101
[Trapper]
Those are vertacines, Mikael.

611
00:29:59,275 --> 00:30:00,450
They're called vertacines.

612
00:30:00,624 --> 00:30:02,104
- Um, are they a problem?
- [mouthing]

613
00:30:02,191 --> 00:30:03,711
[Trapper] No.
They're totally harmless.

614
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:05,344
Unless you get 'em riled up,
and then they pack

615
00:30:05,367 --> 00:30:07,208
about a lightning bolt
worth of bioelectricity.

616
00:30:07,718 --> 00:30:10,460
[screeching]

617
00:30:10,634 --> 00:30:12,417
Predators know
to stay well away.

618
00:30:12,592 --> 00:30:15,290
Which makes them
the perfect chaperone

619
00:30:15,464 --> 00:30:18,642
if you happen to have
a cool biomimicry camouflage.

620
00:30:18,816 --> 00:30:19,948
Which we do.

621
00:30:27,825 --> 00:30:28,869
[vertacines calling]

622
00:30:32,002 --> 00:30:34,875
[alarm blaring in distance]

623
00:30:35,049 --> 00:30:36,809
- Talk to me.
- [tech analyst] It's not good.

624
00:30:36,877 --> 00:30:38,880
Godzilla just made landfall
in France.

625
00:30:39,054 --> 00:30:40,294
Ground team is five klicks out.

626
00:30:46,451 --> 00:30:48,019
[thrilling music playing]

627
00:30:48,192 --> 00:30:49,891
[soldier speaking French]

628
00:30:56,506 --> 00:30:58,900
[in English] We got picture.

629
00:30:59,074 --> 00:31:01,510
[Hampton] Oh, my God.
It's a nuclear facility.

630
00:31:01,684 --> 00:31:02,903
[thrilling music continues]

631
00:31:13,958 --> 00:31:15,525
[soldier 2 speaking French]

632
00:31:26,578 --> 00:31:27,861
[tech analyst in English]
Atmospheric radiation levels

633
00:31:27,884 --> 00:31:29,125
are dropping.
He's absorbing it.

634
00:31:29,191 --> 00:31:30,510
Okay, he's charging
for something.

635
00:31:33,891 --> 00:31:35,674
[energy charging]

636
00:31:41,550 --> 00:31:43,117
[roaring]

637
00:31:49,863 --> 00:31:51,038
[roaring]

638
00:31:52,431 --> 00:31:54,259
[roaring]

639
00:31:54,432 --> 00:31:55,826
[explosion]

640
00:31:56,826 --> 00:31:58,175
[energy powering up]

641
00:31:58,349 --> 00:32:00,221
[nuclear pulse blasts]

642
00:32:02,701 --> 00:32:04,835
[roaring]

643
00:32:07,403 --> 00:32:08,770
[Hampton, distorted]
Godzilla consumed

644
00:32:08,795 --> 00:32:10,362
a huge amount of radiation.

645
00:32:10,536 --> 00:32:13,060
He is clearly preparing
for something...

646
00:32:13,234 --> 00:32:14,061
[automated voice]
Out of range.

647
00:32:14,236 --> 00:32:15,540
Damn it.

648
00:32:15,714 --> 00:32:17,760
[Mikael] We're coming up
on Outpost One.

649
00:32:17,934 --> 00:32:19,849
[engine accelerating]

650
00:32:20,023 --> 00:32:21,939
[vertacines screeching]

651
00:32:26,856 --> 00:32:28,554
Oh, God.

652
00:32:28,728 --> 00:32:30,728
Oh, well, now. That doesn't
look good now, does it?

653
00:32:31,209 --> 00:32:32,427
[Mikael] You seeing this, Doc?

654
00:32:33,732 --> 00:32:34,907
Yeah. Yeah, I'm seeing it.

655
00:32:49,052 --> 00:32:51,098
[suspenseful music playing]

656
00:33:01,065 --> 00:33:02,109
[electricity crackling]

657
00:33:04,634 --> 00:33:06,940
Well, there's
no heat signatures.

658
00:33:07,115 --> 00:33:08,811
So much for survivors.

659
00:33:08,986 --> 00:33:12,163
God, have some respect.
These people had families.

660
00:33:12,336 --> 00:33:13,656
[sighs]
What could have done this?

661
00:33:14,904 --> 00:33:16,602
I don't understand,

662
00:33:16,776 --> 00:33:18,450
we've had this outpost
for years without incident.

663
00:33:18,473 --> 00:33:20,998
So, why attack now?
What changed?

664
00:33:26,307 --> 00:33:29,310
Hey, Doc.
There's a camera here.

665
00:33:29,484 --> 00:33:32,052
You reckon you can pull
any footage off of that?

666
00:33:33,009 --> 00:33:34,055
Oh, shit.

667
00:33:37,884 --> 00:33:39,972
[foreboding music playing]

668
00:33:40,147 --> 00:33:42,324
You think Kong did that?

669
00:33:42,498 --> 00:33:45,631
No, that's not Kong.
That's something else.

670
00:33:45,805 --> 00:33:48,329
Yeah.
Let's get off the ground

671
00:33:48,503 --> 00:33:50,288
before that something else
comes back.

672
00:33:50,461 --> 00:33:51,942
[Mikael] Saddle up.
Let's hustle.

673
00:33:53,116 --> 00:33:54,465
[foreboding music swells]

674
00:33:59,297 --> 00:34:00,603
[Kong grunts]

675
00:34:05,999 --> 00:34:07,087
[grunts inquisitively]

676
00:34:12,309 --> 00:34:14,268
[distant roar]

677
00:34:16,967 --> 00:34:18,621
[grunting]

678
00:34:21,362 --> 00:34:23,626
[thrilling music playing]

679
00:34:29,980 --> 00:34:31,286
[Kong grunts]

680
00:34:39,858 --> 00:34:41,295
[roaring]

681
00:34:46,083 --> 00:34:47,650
[loud thud echoes]

682
00:34:51,001 --> 00:34:52,655
[battle axe humming]

683
00:34:57,398 --> 00:34:59,574
[mystical music playing]

684
00:35:09,541 --> 00:35:10,847
[somber music playing]

685
00:35:11,021 --> 00:35:12,327
[Kong groans]

686
00:35:14,110 --> 00:35:15,199
[distant roar echoes]

687
00:35:27,210 --> 00:35:28,342
[stirring music playing]

688
00:35:38,090 --> 00:35:39,440
[sniffing]

689
00:35:40,876 --> 00:35:42,791
[growls]

690
00:35:42,965 --> 00:35:44,358
[suspenseful music playing]

691
00:35:46,490 --> 00:35:47,884
[growls]

692
00:35:56,675 --> 00:35:57,936
[gasps]

693
00:36:01,811 --> 00:36:03,072
[cooing]

694
00:36:07,947 --> 00:36:09,079
[mini-Kong shudders]

695
00:36:13,605 --> 00:36:14,824
[grunts softly]

696
00:36:17,086 --> 00:36:18,740
[whimpers softly]

697
00:36:22,135 --> 00:36:24,746
[mini-Kong hesitating]

698
00:36:26,617 --> 00:36:28,619
- [mini-Kong snarling]
- [groans]

699
00:36:28,793 --> 00:36:30,405
[mini-Kong screeching]

700
00:36:34,103 --> 00:36:35,235
[Kong growls]

701
00:36:38,150 --> 00:36:39,456
[growling]

702
00:36:41,284 --> 00:36:42,286
[Kong and apes growling]

703
00:36:43,635 --> 00:36:45,114
[straining, grunts]

704
00:36:45,768 --> 00:36:47,291
[growls]

705
00:36:50,119 --> 00:36:51,251
[growls]

706
00:36:52,731 --> 00:36:53,731
[all grunting]

707
00:36:54,864 --> 00:36:55,952
[ape 1 growls]

708
00:37:00,826 --> 00:37:01,826
[snarls]

709
00:37:06,657 --> 00:37:08,485
- [mini-Kong screeching]
- [Kong grunting]

710
00:37:08,659 --> 00:37:10,009
[snarling]

711
00:37:12,838 --> 00:37:14,666
[mini-Kong yelping]

712
00:37:17,103 --> 00:37:19,454
[mini-Kong yelping, growls]

713
00:37:31,378 --> 00:37:32,728
[Kong grunting]

714
00:37:37,559 --> 00:37:38,559
[ape 2 snarls]

715
00:37:42,172 --> 00:37:43,826
[ape 2 screams]

716
00:37:47,264 --> 00:37:48,309
[growls]

717
00:37:50,048 --> 00:37:51,181
[ape 1 gasps]

718
00:38:00,364 --> 00:38:01,496
[groans]

719
00:38:02,409 --> 00:38:03,409
[flapping lips]

720
00:38:03,932 --> 00:38:05,237
[snarls]

721
00:38:12,463 --> 00:38:13,681
[mini-Kong growling]

722
00:38:15,945 --> 00:38:17,250
[roaring]

723
00:38:18,730 --> 00:38:19,730
[screeches]

724
00:38:25,257 --> 00:38:26,434
[sniffs]

725
00:38:28,739 --> 00:38:30,045
- [Kong grunts]
- [whimpering]

726
00:38:32,135 --> 00:38:33,266
[squeals]

727
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:35,094
- [Kong roars]
- [whimpers]

728
00:38:36,139 --> 00:38:37,793
[squawking]

729
00:38:37,967 --> 00:38:39,228
[Kong roars]

730
00:38:47,672 --> 00:38:48,804
[dramatic music playing]

731
00:38:54,853 --> 00:38:56,376
[tablet trilling]

732
00:38:57,289 --> 00:38:58,596
[Ilene sighs]

733
00:38:58,769 --> 00:39:00,139
Are you getting
anything off that thing?

734
00:39:00,163 --> 00:39:01,163
Yeah, I'm just...

735
00:39:03,992 --> 00:39:04,992
Oh, my God.

736
00:39:05,081 --> 00:39:06,081
What?

737
00:39:07,474 --> 00:39:09,780
Here. Take a look.

738
00:39:09,954 --> 00:39:12,436
It looks like an ape.
But that's impossible.

739
00:39:12,610 --> 00:39:14,786
What the bloody hell is that?

740
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:16,092
I have no idea.

741
00:39:16,266 --> 00:39:18,050
[signal glitching]

742
00:39:18,224 --> 00:39:20,226
- Whoa! No! [screams]
- [Ilene] Whoa.

743
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:22,097
[Trapper] Mikael! Mikael!

744
00:39:22,271 --> 00:39:23,490
I'm working on it!

745
00:39:23,664 --> 00:39:24,840
Come on, you...

746
00:39:25,014 --> 00:39:26,213
[Bernie] God!
Okay, okay, okay!

747
00:39:26,318 --> 00:39:27,358
[engine thrusters roaring]

748
00:39:30,148 --> 00:39:31,193
The hell was that, Mikael?

749
00:39:31,367 --> 00:39:33,021
Calm down. Calm down.

750
00:39:33,195 --> 00:39:34,826
It must've been the signal.
The same electrical

751
00:39:34,849 --> 00:39:35,956
disturbances were
happening at the outpost.

752
00:39:35,981 --> 00:39:37,025
[in sign language]

753
00:39:37,199 --> 00:39:39,027
[Bernie] Oh, come on. Come on.

754
00:39:41,813 --> 00:39:43,815
[sighs heavily]

755
00:39:43,989 --> 00:39:45,668
She says it's coming
from that ridge point.

756
00:39:51,257 --> 00:39:52,650
Well, let's take a look.

757
00:39:52,824 --> 00:39:54,224
[Mikael]
I'll get as close as I can.

758
00:39:57,045 --> 00:39:58,829
[door whirring and hissing]

759
00:39:59,831 --> 00:40:01,311
[birds calling]

760
00:40:03,487 --> 00:40:05,619
[mysterious music playing]

761
00:40:08,753 --> 00:40:10,146
[gasps in disbelief]

762
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:11,887
The Hollow Earth.

763
00:40:12,061 --> 00:40:13,496
[gasps]

764
00:40:13,670 --> 00:40:17,195
A world untouched by mankind.

765
00:40:17,369 --> 00:40:19,677
Is this how Neil Armstrong felt

766
00:40:19,851 --> 00:40:21,983
when he stepped on alien soil?

767
00:40:24,072 --> 00:40:26,597
[over video]
Is this one small step for me,

768
00:40:26,771 --> 00:40:27,858
and one giant leap for...

769
00:40:28,032 --> 00:40:29,208
Who are you talking to?

770
00:40:29,382 --> 00:40:30,862
Are you kidding me?

771
00:40:31,036 --> 00:40:32,733
Right down the lens?
It's a documentary.

772
00:40:32,907 --> 00:40:34,755
You wanna be natural.
Just walk, if you just walk.

773
00:40:34,778 --> 00:40:36,364
- All right, just keep...
- Yeah, just... Okay. Take two.

774
00:40:36,389 --> 00:40:38,304
[Bernie clears throat]

775
00:40:38,478 --> 00:40:43,047
The Hollow Earth. A world...

776
00:40:43,222 --> 00:40:45,199
[Mikael] All right, guys.
That ridge you pointed out

777
00:40:45,224 --> 00:40:46,704
is about two miles
straight ahead.

778
00:40:50,273 --> 00:40:51,492
[mosquitos buzzing]

779
00:40:51,666 --> 00:40:52,945
I'm getting eaten alive
out here.

780
00:40:53,101 --> 00:40:54,885
[mosquito buzzing]

781
00:40:55,059 --> 00:40:58,193
Oh, look at that.
I must be tasty too.

782
00:40:59,195 --> 00:41:00,195
Kill it.

783
00:41:01,675 --> 00:41:04,242
Only female mosquitos
drink blood.

784
00:41:04,416 --> 00:41:05,722
So they can grow their eggs.

785
00:41:05,896 --> 00:41:07,943
[mosquito buzzing]

786
00:41:08,117 --> 00:41:09,465
She needs it more than me.

787
00:41:11,728 --> 00:41:12,809
[captivating music playing]

788
00:41:24,916 --> 00:41:27,092
[Trapper] Wait.

789
00:41:27,266 --> 00:41:29,746
- [Ilene] What?
- What's the holdup?

790
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:31,226
Not this way.

791
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:33,141
What? Why?

792
00:41:33,315 --> 00:41:34,771
Yeah, we gotta take a detour.
There's something here.

793
00:41:34,795 --> 00:41:36,927
Where, here? Like here, here?

794
00:41:37,101 --> 00:41:39,190
[Ilene] Hey.

795
00:41:39,364 --> 00:41:41,106
Nah. I'm not picking
anything up.

796
00:41:41,280 --> 00:41:42,599
No. Something
doesn't smell right,

797
00:41:42,672 --> 00:41:44,108
and it's not just you, Mikael.

798
00:41:44,282 --> 00:41:47,199
Can you smell that?
It's like rotting flesh.

799
00:41:47,373 --> 00:41:49,375
It's probably
just a carcass upwind.

800
00:41:49,550 --> 00:41:50,657
- We keep moving.
- Mikael, hold up.

801
00:41:50,681 --> 00:41:52,639
Listen, pal. I'm gonna trust

802
00:41:52,813 --> 00:41:54,641
my state of the art thermal
over your

803
00:41:54,815 --> 00:41:57,121
Ace Ventura
hippie-dippie sixth sense

804
00:41:57,295 --> 00:41:59,342
all day long. You got me?

805
00:41:59,516 --> 00:42:00,927
There's no need to call
people names. We're just...

806
00:42:00,952 --> 00:42:02,518
Hey. And as for you,
freak show,

807
00:42:02,693 --> 00:42:04,541
if you don't shut it,
I'm gonna take that camera,

808
00:42:04,565 --> 00:42:05,672
I'm gonna shove it
right up your arse.

809
00:42:05,695 --> 00:42:07,132
I'm in charge, we move.

810
00:42:07,306 --> 00:42:08,501
Why don't we just listen
to somebody calmer?

811
00:42:08,525 --> 00:42:09,786
I said I'm in charge.

812
00:42:09,960 --> 00:42:11,527
I'm in charge! [yells]

813
00:42:11,702 --> 00:42:12,876
- [Bernie] Whoa!
- [all gasp]

814
00:42:13,050 --> 00:42:14,443
- Run!
- [screams]

815
00:42:15,271 --> 00:42:16,706
[tree crunching]

816
00:42:16,880 --> 00:42:18,360
- [Bernie whimpering]
- [tree belches]

817
00:42:19,884 --> 00:42:21,166
[Bernie] It was a tree.
It was a tree!

818
00:42:21,190 --> 00:42:22,844
[Trapper] Wait, wait, wait.

819
00:42:23,018 --> 00:42:24,342
We should be all right.
We should be all right.

820
00:42:24,367 --> 00:42:25,605
Those things
don't reach that far.

821
00:42:25,628 --> 00:42:26,978
He was just eaten by a tree.

822
00:42:27,152 --> 00:42:28,826
- [Trapper] What you doing, Doc?
- [radio beeps]

823
00:42:28,849 --> 00:42:30,523
[Ilene] I'm trying to call
the Base for extraction.

824
00:42:30,547 --> 00:42:32,003
[Bernie] It's just, one minute
he was there, right?

825
00:42:32,027 --> 00:42:33,177
He was right in my face.
And then, a tree!

826
00:42:33,202 --> 00:42:33,985
- Outta nowhere!
- I know, man.

827
00:42:34,159 --> 00:42:35,333
I know. That's heavy.

828
00:42:35,507 --> 00:42:36,248
But that's
the natural world, man.

829
00:42:36,422 --> 00:42:37,597
"Red in tooth and claw."

830
00:42:37,771 --> 00:42:39,817
Tennyson.
You just watched a man

831
00:42:39,990 --> 00:42:41,557
