1193
01:09:42,132 --> 01:09:43,961
[energy charging up]

1194
01:09:44,135 --> 01:09:45,224
[mini-Kong screeching]

1195
01:09:56,322 --> 01:09:58,759
[apes screeching]

1196
01:10:03,894 --> 01:10:05,809
[Ilene] Trapped within
their subterranean realm,

1197
01:10:05,983 --> 01:10:08,551
the Skar King harnessed
a terrible power.

1198
01:10:08,725 --> 01:10:11,032
The ancient Titan, Shimo.

1199
01:10:11,206 --> 01:10:13,774
[Shimo screeching]

1200
01:10:15,515 --> 01:10:18,692
[Ilene] He controls her
with pain.

1201
01:10:18,865 --> 01:10:20,746
Her power covered the Earth
in the last ice age.

1202
01:10:23,217 --> 01:10:25,002
We brought Kong down here.

1203
01:10:25,176 --> 01:10:26,815
He's been looking
for others like himself,

1204
01:10:26,873 --> 01:10:28,354
going deeper into Hollow Earth

1205
01:10:28,528 --> 01:10:30,791
and getting closer
to their prison.

1206
01:10:30,965 --> 01:10:33,045
The Iwi must have known
it was just a matter of time,

1207
01:10:33,096 --> 01:10:34,837
and that's why they've been

1208
01:10:35,011 --> 01:10:38,059
calling for help, and that's
why Godzilla's changing.

1209
01:10:38,233 --> 01:10:39,712
He's gearing up
for World War Three.

1210
01:10:39,886 --> 01:10:41,497
Okay, but he barely survived
last time.

1211
01:10:41,671 --> 01:10:43,150
What's Godzilla
gonna do on his own?

1212
01:10:45,239 --> 01:10:48,287
He won't be on his own.

1213
01:10:48,461 --> 01:10:51,114
The Iwi believe
that at the end of the world,

1214
01:10:51,289 --> 01:10:53,682
one of their own will return...

1215
01:10:53,856 --> 01:10:57,121
and awaken Mothra,
defender of the Iwi...

1216
01:10:57,296 --> 01:10:59,863
and ancient ally of Godzilla.

1217
01:11:00,037 --> 01:11:02,082
They believe
that their savior will be

1218
01:11:02,256 --> 01:11:03,649
an Iwi from Skull Island.

1219
01:11:07,043 --> 01:11:08,916
That seems like a lot
to put on one kid.

1220
01:11:16,140 --> 01:11:18,533
[dramatic music playing]

1221
01:11:18,707 --> 01:11:20,493
[creatures screeching]

1222
01:11:24,192 --> 01:11:26,194
[apes growling]

1223
01:11:45,082 --> 01:11:46,387
[gasps]

1224
01:11:50,131 --> 01:11:51,131
[growling]

1225
01:11:55,614 --> 01:11:56,614
[groans]

1226
01:12:07,670 --> 01:12:09,890
[apes growling]

1227
01:12:20,770 --> 01:12:22,250
[ape grunts]

1228
01:12:27,951 --> 01:12:29,475
[tense music playing]

1229
01:12:37,177 --> 01:12:38,177
[apes shrieking]

1230
01:12:43,792 --> 01:12:45,273
[dramatic music playing]

1231
01:12:49,059 --> 01:12:50,930
[hooting]

1232
01:12:54,020 --> 01:12:55,326
[groans weakly]

1233
01:13:06,729 --> 01:13:08,426
[Kong groaning]

1234
01:13:19,176 --> 01:13:23,136
[ape growls]

1235
01:13:23,310 --> 01:13:24,722
[pilot over radio] This is
Monarch Air Team to Base,

1236
01:13:24,747 --> 01:13:26,706
tracking over
Godzilla's location.

1237
01:13:26,880 --> 01:13:29,448
We've closed the shipping lanes
within 300 miles.

1238
01:13:29,622 --> 01:13:33,189
Plasma readings indicate he's
absorbing everything in there.

1239
01:13:33,363 --> 01:13:35,889
[energy pulsing]

1240
01:13:49,815 --> 01:13:50,922
[Ilene] You know, I made
a deal with myself

1241
01:13:50,947 --> 01:13:53,122
when I became a mother.

1242
01:13:53,296 --> 01:13:56,386
I said to myself, "I don't care
what you have to sacrifice...

1243
01:13:56,561 --> 01:13:59,738
what you have to give up,

1244
01:13:59,912 --> 01:14:01,697
you will do right
by that little girl."

1245
01:14:01,871 --> 01:14:03,655
[children laughing]

1246
01:14:05,091 --> 01:14:06,572
I just never thought that

1247
01:14:06,746 --> 01:14:09,139
the thing I'd be giving up
would be her.

1248
01:14:09,313 --> 01:14:10,706
Look, you don't know that.

1249
01:14:10,880 --> 01:14:11,881
Really?

1250
01:14:12,055 --> 01:14:13,578
Trapper, before we came here

1251
01:14:13,752 --> 01:14:16,798
she said that
she didn't belong anywhere.

1252
01:14:16,972 --> 01:14:19,801
If this is the life
that she wants,

1253
01:14:19,975 --> 01:14:21,412
then I have to give her up.

1254
01:14:29,115 --> 01:14:31,900
[rumbling]

1255
01:14:32,074 --> 01:14:33,599
[Trapper] Am I having
a funny turn

1256
01:14:33,773 --> 01:14:34,880
or does everything feel
lighter down here?

1257
01:14:34,904 --> 01:14:36,601
[Bernie mumbles incoherently]

1258
01:14:36,775 --> 01:14:37,815
[Bernie] Wait, wait, wait.

1259
01:14:39,126 --> 01:14:40,953
[Bernie gasps, chuckles]

1260
01:14:41,127 --> 01:14:43,304
[Trapper] What are they doing?
That must weigh a ton.

1261
01:14:43,478 --> 01:14:44,739
[Bernie] Yeah. Yeah, see,

1262
01:14:44,913 --> 01:14:46,786
I don't know
how they can do it...

1263
01:14:46,960 --> 01:14:48,372
but somehow they're able to
move the pyramids' positions,

1264
01:14:48,395 --> 01:14:49,744
which disrupts the

1265
01:14:49,918 --> 01:14:51,617
gravitational pull down here,

1266
01:14:51,791 --> 01:14:53,574
and that's how
they run their city.

1267
01:14:53,748 --> 01:14:55,315
An entire civilization

1268
01:14:55,489 --> 01:14:57,100
built off the manipulation
of gravity.

1269
01:14:57,274 --> 01:14:59,625
God, I wish
was streaming this live!

1270
01:14:59,798 --> 01:15:01,118
What you gonna do
with that, Bern?

1271
01:15:02,931 --> 01:15:04,760
Look, I know
what you're thinking,

1272
01:15:04,934 --> 01:15:06,935
but you don't understand.
Okay?

1273
01:15:07,109 --> 01:15:08,217
To have been through
what I've been through,

1274
01:15:08,242 --> 01:15:09,721
seen what I seen

1275
01:15:09,895 --> 01:15:11,416
and have absolutely
nobody believe you.

1276
01:15:13,333 --> 01:15:15,640
This place...

1277
01:15:15,814 --> 01:15:19,208
This place is special, man.
It's magic.

1278
01:15:19,382 --> 01:15:21,023
How long do you think
it'll stay like that

1279
01:15:21,123 --> 01:15:23,212
if you start posting that
about, hmm?

1280
01:15:23,386 --> 01:15:26,782
Like, you look at any isolated
tribe or community,

1281
01:15:26,956 --> 01:15:28,479
how many of them

1282
01:15:28,654 --> 01:15:30,373
survive contact with
the outside world, hmm?

1283
01:15:33,222 --> 01:15:35,181
You know I think
you're brilliant, don't you?

1284
01:15:35,355 --> 01:15:37,140
You already saved
the world once.

1285
01:15:37,314 --> 01:15:38,514
Can't take that away from you.

1286
01:15:40,882 --> 01:15:42,405
Could you say that all again?

1287
01:15:42,581 --> 01:15:44,278
The last part,
so I have it on footage.

1288
01:15:44,452 --> 01:15:45,627
What?

1289
01:15:45,801 --> 01:15:48,108
[horn bellows]

1290
01:15:48,282 --> 01:15:50,588
Oh, well, we have to find out
what that was, right?

1291
01:15:58,684 --> 01:16:00,773
[people grunting]

1292
01:16:14,307 --> 01:16:15,613
[chattering]

1293
01:16:24,318 --> 01:16:25,318
[snorts]

1294
01:16:28,234 --> 01:16:29,234
Oh, my God.

1295
01:16:32,673 --> 01:16:34,894
[Kong grunts, snorts]

1296
01:16:37,722 --> 01:16:39,376
[Bernie] Is that a mini-Kong?

1297
01:16:41,726 --> 01:16:43,032
How did they find this place?

1298
01:16:43,206 --> 01:16:44,555
He must have sensed Jia.

1299
01:16:48,515 --> 01:16:49,690
[groans weakly]

1300
01:16:50,909 --> 01:16:52,085
[mini-Kong exclaims]

1301
01:16:59,787 --> 01:17:01,268
[muffled, weak heartbeat]

1302
01:17:14,585 --> 01:17:16,369
[somber music playing]

1303
01:17:28,077 --> 01:17:31,385
[in sign language]

1304
01:17:40,088 --> 01:17:41,307
[Ilene] That arm looks bad.

1305
01:17:41,481 --> 01:17:43,570
Yeah. That's worse than bad.

1306
01:17:44,572 --> 01:17:45,573
That's frostbite.

1307
01:17:45,747 --> 01:17:47,314
[chatters softly]

1308
01:17:50,838 --> 01:17:51,926
I'd better go take a look.

1309
01:17:54,756 --> 01:17:57,323
[chattering violently]

1310
01:17:59,020 --> 01:18:01,067
[music swells]

1311
01:18:07,595 --> 01:18:09,596
[grunting]

1312
01:18:15,471 --> 01:18:16,646
[snarls]

1313
01:18:23,219 --> 01:18:24,264
[apes whimper]

1314
01:18:28,136 --> 01:18:30,139
[roars]

1315
01:18:35,448 --> 01:18:37,189
[roars]

1316
01:18:55,555 --> 01:18:57,775
[powering up]

1317
01:19:12,311 --> 01:19:14,182
[roars]

1318
01:19:21,582 --> 01:19:23,734
[female automated voice] Warning, detecting
altered energy signature.

1319
01:19:23,757 --> 01:19:26,500
[Hampton] Oh, my God.
He's changed.

1320
01:19:30,765 --> 01:19:32,940
[grunts weakly]

1321
01:19:33,114 --> 01:19:35,988
I know, I know.
Nobody likes a dentist.

1322
01:19:37,945 --> 01:19:39,686
Let's get a look
at that arm, big guy.

1323
01:19:40,644 --> 01:19:41,819
[device trilling]

1324
01:19:44,038 --> 01:19:45,779
Trapper, he looks really hurt.

1325
01:19:45,953 --> 01:19:48,913
Yeah, it's not great.
I'm seeing nerve damage...

1326
01:19:49,087 --> 01:19:51,480
significant tissue loss.

1327
01:19:51,654 --> 01:19:53,439
[Ilene]
So, what are we saying?

1328
01:19:53,613 --> 01:19:56,443
He's not gonna last a day down
here with only one arm.

1329
01:19:56,617 --> 01:19:58,966
Yeah, communication
to the surface is still out.

1330
01:19:59,140 --> 01:20:00,447
If I can get back
to the outpost,

1331
01:20:00,621 --> 01:20:01,728
I think there might be
some supplies

1332
01:20:01,752 --> 01:20:03,623
that we can use.

1333
01:20:03,797 --> 01:20:05,253
I don't think a massive cast
is gonna solve the problem.

1334
01:20:05,278 --> 01:20:08,149
I wasn't talkin'
plaster of Paris.

1335
01:20:08,323 --> 01:20:10,003
I'm thinking
more along the lines of, uh...

1336
01:20:12,154 --> 01:20:13,460
Project Powerhouse.

1337
01:20:13,634 --> 01:20:14,765
[thrilling music playing]

1338
01:20:14,939 --> 01:20:15,939
You can't be serious?

1339
01:20:15,984 --> 01:20:18,073
Oh, I'm deadly serious.

1340
01:20:18,247 --> 01:20:19,900
That prototype
was almost finished

1341
01:20:20,074 --> 01:20:21,597
when they pulled the funding.

1342
01:20:21,771 --> 01:20:23,612
All right, well, what are you
still doing here?

1343
01:20:23,644 --> 01:20:26,037
I love you, too, Doc.

1344
01:20:26,212 --> 01:20:28,735
Project Powerhouse, what is...
what is that, exactly?

1345
01:20:31,957 --> 01:20:33,567
[Ilene] After Mechagodzilla,

1346
01:20:33,740 --> 01:20:34,805
we realized that there were
some threats that

1347
01:20:34,828 --> 01:20:36,483
even Kong couldn't face.

1348
01:20:36,657 --> 01:20:40,921
So, we started working on some
minor augmentations.

1349
01:20:41,095 --> 01:20:43,271
Oh.

1350
01:20:43,445 --> 01:20:44,882
Wait, what kind of
augmentations?

1351
01:20:48,320 --> 01:20:49,951
[Ilene] Making one of
the strongest Titans

1352
01:20:49,975 --> 01:20:51,801
even stronger
didn't go over so well.

1353
01:20:51,976 --> 01:20:53,064
So, we got shut down.

1354
01:20:56,981 --> 01:20:58,809
Lucky for us, the prototype

1355
01:20:58,984 --> 01:21:01,987
had already been transported
to Hollow Earth for testing.

1356
01:21:02,161 --> 01:21:05,773
It's stored in the armory
at Outpost One.

1357
01:21:05,947 --> 01:21:08,079
[music swells, ends]

1358
01:21:10,820 --> 01:21:13,085
["I Was Made
For Lovin' You" playing]

1359
01:21:18,480 --> 01:21:20,221
[laughs]

1360
01:21:20,395 --> 01:21:25,010
♪ Tonight, I want
To give it all to you ♪

1361
01:21:25,184 --> 01:21:26,856
[female automated voice]
Autopilot engaged.

1362
01:21:26,881 --> 01:21:30,319
[machinery whirring]

1363
01:21:30,493 --> 01:21:33,931
♪ There's so much
I want to do ♪

1364
01:21:34,105 --> 01:21:37,543
♪ I was made
For lovin' you, baby ♪

1365
01:21:37,717 --> 01:21:40,850
♪ You were made
For lovin' me ♪

1366
01:21:41,025 --> 01:21:42,853
[groans in pain]

1367
01:21:43,028 --> 01:21:44,115
Woo-hoo!

1368
01:21:45,944 --> 01:21:47,596
What do you think of that?

1369
01:21:47,770 --> 01:21:49,730
That's one hell of an
augmentation there, Trapper.

1370
01:21:49,904 --> 01:21:51,949
[Trapper]
Only the best for Mr. Kong.

1371
01:21:53,429 --> 01:21:55,649
[ice crackling]

1372
01:22:00,740 --> 01:22:03,483
[both roar]

1373
01:22:08,530 --> 01:22:09,530
[chattering]

1374
01:22:14,667 --> 01:22:15,842
[grunts softly]

1375
01:22:16,016 --> 01:22:17,409
All right, it's ready to go.

1376
01:22:20,456 --> 01:22:22,545
Those injections should heal
the frostbite up nicely.

1377
01:22:22,719 --> 01:22:24,158
[augmentation crackling,
powering up]

1378
01:22:32,381 --> 01:22:34,078
[Bernie]
All right, there he goes.

1379
01:22:34,252 --> 01:22:35,252
He's moving.

1380
01:22:39,909 --> 01:22:40,909
[Bernie] You got this.

1381
01:22:42,216 --> 01:22:43,216
[Kong grunts]

1382
01:22:50,269 --> 01:22:51,985
Look, it's a bit rough
and ready, but it should hold.

1383
01:22:52,010 --> 01:22:53,073
It's good.
It looks good, Trapper.

1384
01:22:53,097 --> 01:22:54,097
Damn good.

1385
01:22:54,751 --> 01:22:56,622
[snorts, snarls]

1386
01:23:02,063 --> 01:23:03,978
- Here we go.
- Yeah.

1387
01:23:04,152 --> 01:23:05,457
He's either gonna love it

1388
01:23:05,631 --> 01:23:07,192
or he's gonna rip it off
with his teeth.

1389
01:23:10,070 --> 01:23:11,551
[roars]

1390
01:23:13,814 --> 01:23:16,425
[exclaims] I think
he loves it! Yeah?

1391
01:23:22,256 --> 01:23:23,737
[mini-Kong grunts, chatters]

1392
01:23:35,574 --> 01:23:37,751
[grunts]

1393
01:23:38,795 --> 01:23:39,796
Skar King.

1394
01:23:43,974 --> 01:23:45,323
[grunts]

1395
01:23:45,497 --> 01:23:47,238
Hey, hey!
What did you tell him?

1396
01:23:48,369 --> 01:23:50,154
[in sign language]

1397
01:23:50,328 --> 01:23:51,939
Oh.

1398
01:23:53,287 --> 01:23:54,854
[Bernie]
Where's he going?

1399
01:23:55,029 --> 01:23:57,162
Godzilla won't come down here
unless Kong brings him.

1400
01:23:57,336 --> 01:23:58,661
[Bernie] Okay, the last time
those two met up

1401
01:23:58,685 --> 01:24:00,381
it was almost the end of Kong.

1402
01:24:00,555 --> 01:24:02,115
[Trapper]
He is taking a hell of a risk.

1403
01:24:04,342 --> 01:24:07,171
If Kong invades his turf,
could start a war.

1404
01:24:07,345 --> 01:24:09,652
Yeah, that's a suicide mission.

1405
01:24:09,826 --> 01:24:12,090
But if Kong draws Godzilla
down here...

1406
01:24:12,264 --> 01:24:14,309
they can make their stand
in Hollow Earth

1407
01:24:14,483 --> 01:24:16,484
and then there's a chance that

1408
01:24:16,658 --> 01:24:18,487
Godzilla can stop
Skar King and Shimo

1409
01:24:18,661 --> 01:24:19,701
from reaching the surface.

1410
01:24:35,721 --> 01:24:37,158
[indistinct chatter]

1411
01:24:45,252 --> 01:24:47,212
[rumbling]

1412
01:24:51,216 --> 01:24:52,390
[woman exclaims in Arabic]

1413
01:24:55,350 --> 01:24:57,177
- [people clamor]
- [horns honking]

1414
01:25:06,708 --> 01:25:08,145
[people scream]

1415
01:25:20,940 --> 01:25:22,769
[people scream]

1416
01:25:42,048 --> 01:25:43,877
[roars]

1417
01:25:46,880 --> 01:25:48,577
[roars]

1418
01:26:04,592 --> 01:26:06,247
[tense instrumental music
playing]

1419
01:26:20,479 --> 01:26:22,306
We are absolutely certain

1420
01:26:22,480 --> 01:26:24,613
that she can pull this off,
right?

1421
01:26:24,787 --> 01:26:26,702
[Ilene]
It's why Jia was called here.

1422
01:26:26,876 --> 01:26:30,184
Only an Iwi from Skull Island
can awaken Mothra.

1423
01:26:30,358 --> 01:26:32,185
And Mothra is the key
to Godzilla

1424
01:26:32,359 --> 01:26:33,622
protecting this place,

1425
01:26:33,796 --> 01:26:35,581
and its pathways to the surface.

1426
01:26:44,024 --> 01:26:45,344
[softly]
She's gonna be all right.

1427
01:26:45,372 --> 01:26:46,813
- Uh-huh.
- She's gonna be all right.

1428
01:26:51,552 --> 01:26:53,251
[trilling, resonating]

1429
01:27:01,301 --> 01:27:02,302
[Bernie gasps softly]

1430
01:27:04,043 --> 01:27:05,305
[trilling]

1431
01:27:13,574 --> 01:27:15,359
[Mothra moans]

1432
01:27:15,533 --> 01:27:17,318
[musical flourish]

1433
01:27:18,971 --> 01:27:20,278
[chitters]

1434
01:27:24,064 --> 01:27:26,283
[Mothra screeches, clicks]

1435
01:27:34,247 --> 01:27:35,814
[Mothra screeches]

1436
01:27:46,738 --> 01:27:49,002
[Bernie] Hey, she's evacuating
the villagers.

1437
01:27:52,875 --> 01:27:55,095
Gravity! Gravity!
The pyramids and gravity.

1438
01:27:55,269 --> 01:27:57,096
Yeah, I got it! I got it now!

1439
01:27:57,270 --> 01:27:58,814
- [Ilene] Tell me on the way.
- [Bernie] Come on, come on!

1440
01:27:58,837 --> 01:28:00,637
While we are throwing
random shit at the wall,

1441
01:28:00,752 --> 01:28:03,537
permission to take the HEAV?
Rally some reinforcements.

1442
01:28:03,712 --> 01:28:05,112
To the surface?
No, there's no time.

1443
01:28:05,279 --> 01:28:07,890
No, this idea's
way weirder than that.

1444
01:28:08,064 --> 01:28:09,675
[thrilling music playing]

1445
01:28:30,260 --> 01:28:31,739
[growls]

1446
01:28:41,881 --> 01:28:43,229
[snarls]

1447
01:28:43,404 --> 01:28:45,537
[people screaming]

1448
01:28:59,680 --> 01:29:01,073
[grunts]

1449
01:29:01,247 --> 01:29:02,902
[roars]

1450
01:29:19,309 --> 01:29:20,920
[Kong exclaims, grunts]

1451
01:29:31,800 --> 01:29:32,800
[Godzilla groans]

1452
01:29:40,287 --> 01:29:41,287
[augmentation powers up]

1453
01:29:50,166 --> 01:29:51,166
[metal clangs]

1454
01:30:01,350 --> 01:30:04,050
[atomic breath swells]

1455
01:30:18,020 --> 01:30:19,020
[Kong exclaims]

1456
01:30:38,737 --> 01:30:40,520
[atomic breath swells]

1457
01:30:44,350 --> 01:30:45,657
[distant shriek]

1458
01:30:49,225 --> 01:30:50,574
[Mothra moans]

1459
01:30:58,974 --> 01:30:59,974
[Godzilla grunts]

1460
01:31:11,377 --> 01:31:14,076
[screeches]

1461
01:31:14,250 --> 01:31:16,252
[dramatic synth music playing]

1462
01:31:21,039 --> 01:31:22,215
[roars]

1463
01:31:22,389 --> 01:31:24,564
[music swells]

1464
01:31:26,045 --> 01:31:27,872
[roars]

1465
01:31:35,488 --> 01:31:37,099
[suspenseful music playing]

1466
01:31:37,273 --> 01:31:38,989
[Ilene] All right,
we're underneath the pyramids.

1467
01:31:39,014 --> 01:31:40,275
Now what?

1468
01:31:40,449 --> 01:31:42,148
Gravity. [exhales sharply]

1469
01:31:42,322 --> 01:31:43,322
Iwi technology.

1470
01:31:52,113 --> 01:31:53,594
[pulsing]

1471
01:31:57,337 --> 01:31:58,904
With the chemical reaction,

1472
01:31:59,078 --> 01:32:01,210
this liquid metal becomes
an engineering mechanism

1473
01:32:01,384 --> 01:32:03,648
forcing the two
electromagnetic pyramids

1474
01:32:03,822 --> 01:32:05,953
together, causing
an anti-gravity shock wave.

1475
01:32:06,127 --> 01:32:08,478
But only for a few minutes.
Or maybe less.

1476
01:32:08,653 --> 01:32:10,784
Which should keep those
things from the portals.

1477
01:32:10,958 --> 01:32:12,873
After that,
everything that is up

1478
01:32:13,047 --> 01:32:14,092
will come crashing down.

1479
01:32:14,266 --> 01:32:17,530
[rumbling]

1480
01:32:18,488 --> 01:32:20,578
[crackling]

1481
01:32:28,628 --> 01:32:29,628
[apes screeching]

1482
01:32:32,980 --> 01:32:34,461
They're here.
[exhales sharply]

1483
01:32:36,506 --> 01:32:38,813
[tense music playing]

1484
01:32:48,561 --> 01:32:50,128
[roars]

1485
01:32:50,302 --> 01:32:51,783
[Shimo roaring]

1486
01:32:56,309 --> 01:32:59,399
[crackling]

1487
01:32:59,573 --> 01:33:00,984
We're not gonna make it.
There's not enough time.

1488
01:33:01,009 --> 01:33:02,117
We need something
to slow them down.

1489
01:33:02,140 --> 01:33:03,533
Yeah, but what else can we do?

1490
01:33:03,707 --> 01:33:05,360
[vertacine screeching]

1491
01:33:05,534 --> 01:33:07,426
[Trapper over radio]
It's vertacine mating season.

1492
01:33:07,449 --> 01:33:09,975
["Turn Me Loose" playing]

1493
01:33:10,149 --> 01:33:11,932
No way.

1494
01:33:12,106 --> 01:33:14,675
- [laughs]
- ♪ I gotta do it my way ♪

1495
01:33:16,634 --> 01:33:18,199
♪ I want to fly ♪

1496
01:33:18,373 --> 01:33:19,984
[roaring]

1497
01:33:23,030 --> 01:33:25,381
[Bernie yells]

1498
01:33:29,559 --> 01:33:31,038
Your carriage awaits.

1499
01:33:31,212 --> 01:33:32,363
I'm gonna kiss you on the mouth!

1500
01:33:32,387 --> 01:33:33,387
[Ilene] Come on. Go, go.

1501
01:33:36,479 --> 01:33:38,264
Buckle up, you beautiful people.

1502
01:33:38,438 --> 01:33:40,309
Up and away. Yes!

1503
01:33:40,483 --> 01:33:42,703
♪ I gotta do it my way ♪

1504
01:33:44,792 --> 01:33:49,536
♪ I want to fly ♪

1505
01:33:49,710 --> 01:33:51,059
[tense music playing]

1506
01:33:52,146 --> 01:33:53,146
[growls]

1507
01:33:55,454 --> 01:33:56,542
[apes grunt]

1508
01:33:58,065 --> 01:33:59,110
[grunts]

1509
01:34:02,766 --> 01:34:04,551
[rumbling]

1510
01:34:05,203 --> 01:34:06,858
[roars]

1511
01:34:08,467 --> 01:34:09,686
[Kong snarling]

1512
01:34:17,564 --> 01:34:18,783
[roaring]

1513
01:34:21,524 --> 01:34:23,091
[thrilling music playing]

1514
01:34:24,353 --> 01:34:25,398
[roaring]

1515
01:34:39,106 --> 01:34:40,500
[grunts]

1516
01:34:40,673 --> 01:34:41,805
[devices beeping]

1517
01:34:41,979 --> 01:34:43,284
[Trapper] No! The engine's out.

1518
01:34:43,458 --> 01:34:44,609
The gravity surge
must have taken out

1519
01:34:44,634 --> 01:34:46,462
the power-battery-thing.

1520
01:34:46,636 --> 01:34:48,725
[Godzilla roaring]

1521
01:35:01,650 --> 01:35:03,001
[Skar King roars]

1522
01:35:06,873 --> 01:35:08,746
[thrilling music continues]

1523
01:35:11,313 --> 01:35:12,313
[Kong grunts]

1524
01:35:16,841 --> 01:35:18,756
[all screaming]

1525
01:35:21,759 --> 01:35:23,282
[triumphant music playing]

1526
01:35:23,456 --> 01:35:25,371
Yes! Yes!

1527
01:35:25,545 --> 01:35:26,764
She's protecting the portals.

1528
01:35:28,025 --> 01:35:29,025
[Mothra moans]

1529
01:35:33,682 --> 01:35:34,684
[Mothra chitters]

1530
01:35:36,469 --> 01:35:37,948
[grunting]

1531
01:35:39,645 --> 01:35:41,126
[snarls]

1532
01:35:41,300 --> 01:35:42,301
[grunts]

1533
01:35:47,523 --> 01:35:49,176
[thrilling music playing]

1534
01:35:54,703 --> 01:35:55,704
[roars]

1535
01:36:00,536 --> 01:36:01,536
[Mothra screeches]

1536
01:36:02,494 --> 01:36:03,496
[chitters]

1537
01:36:09,894 --> 01:36:10,894
[roars]

1538
01:36:13,898 --> 01:36:14,898
[Skar King grunts]

1539
01:36:16,509 --> 01:36:18,423
[Kong roars]

1540
01:36:24,125 --> 01:36:25,125
[mini-Kong grunting]

1541
01:36:30,305 --> 01:36:31,305
[grunts]

1542
01:36:34,309 --> 01:36:35,832
[thrilling music continues]

1543
01:36:38,573 --> 01:36:39,880
[shouting] Oh, God!

1544
01:36:41,707 --> 01:36:42,840
[Mothra screeches]

1545
01:36:47,713 --> 01:36:48,757
[Bernie grunts]

1546
01:36:48,932 --> 01:36:51,717
[Bernie laughs nervously] Oh.

1547
01:36:55,721 --> 01:36:57,898
[roaring]

1548
01:37:00,640 --> 01:37:01,945
[Kong roars]

1549
01:37:06,385 --> 01:37:07,472
[roars]

1550
01:37:16,090 --> 01:37:17,962
["Samba Toff" playing]

1551
01:37:21,095 --> 01:37:22,400
[rumbling]

1552
01:37:26,666 --> 01:37:28,407
[crackling]

1553
01:37:35,979 --> 01:37:37,764
["Samba Toff" slows down]

1554
01:37:42,595 --> 01:37:43,944
[Godzilla roars]

1555
01:37:57,827 --> 01:37:59,176
[grunting]

1556
01:38:01,657 --> 01:38:03,354
[tense music playing]

1557
01:38:08,055 --> 01:38:09,055
[growls]

1558
01:38:12,319 --> 01:38:15,323
[roaring]

1559
01:38:15,497 --> 01:38:17,456
[people screaming]

1560
01:38:22,851 --> 01:38:24,942
[ice breath swells]

1561
01:38:32,426 --> 01:38:33,993
[tense music continues]

1562
01:38:36,735 --> 01:38:38,042
[windows shattering]

1563
01:38:41,654 --> 01:38:43,002
[roaring]

1564
01:38:49,662 --> 01:38:50,967
[rumbling]

1565
01:38:52,664 --> 01:38:55,145
[roaring]

1566
01:38:57,060 --> 01:38:58,409
[grunts, spits]

1567
01:39:00,542 --> 01:39:02,065
- [people screaming]
- [horns honking]

1568
01:39:04,242 --> 01:39:05,983
[thrilling music playing]

1569
01:39:13,903 --> 01:39:15,252
